{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Jelly","content":["Place a ceramic or glass bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh water into it. Add gelatine and set aside to soak for 5 minutes or until spongy.","Place wine, apple juice and sugar into mixing bowl and heat <b>10 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid.","Add reserved gelatine mixture and mix <b>30 sec\/50°C\/speed 2<b>, or until dissolved. Transfer mixture into a bowl and set aside to cool completely to room temperature (approx. 1 hour). Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Sponge","content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Grease and line a cake tin (20 x 30 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Place sugar into mixing bowl and mill <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Add eggs and vanilla and whisk <b>15 min\/speed 4<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>.","Add bicarbonate of soda, cream of tartar and cornflour and combine <b>50 sec\/\/speed 1<b>. Transfer mixture into prepared tin and bake for 30 minutes (180°C), or until a wooden skewer inserted into the centre of the sponge comes out clean. Clean and dry mixing bowl and butterfly whisk.","Leave sponge to cool in tin for 5 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack to cool completely. Once cake has cooled, cut into 30 fingers (2 x 10 cm) and set aside."]},{"title":"Custard","content":["Place  sugar and cornflour into mixing bowl and mill <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add eggs, milk and vanilla and cook <b>10 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b>, or until thickened. Transfer into a bowl. Cover surface with baking paper and set aside to cool for 10 minutes, then place into refrigerator to cool completely (approx. 1 hour). Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["Line a glass trifle bowl (20 cm) with one-third of the sponge fingers and spoon over one-third of the jelly (approx. 400 g). Set aside to soak for 5 minutes.","Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh half of the blackberry jam (75 g)  into it. Spoon jam over sponge. Sprinkle with one-third of the almonds and one-quarter of the mixed berries.","Place cold custard into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>, or until smooth. Spread half of the custard over berries.","Layer with another one-third of the sponge, one-third (400 g) of the jelly, remaining 75 g jam, one-third of the almonds, one-quarter of the berries and remaining half of the custard. Top with remaining sponge, remaining jelly and one-quarter of the berries. Clean and dry mixing bowl."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream into mixing bowl and whip <b>until soft peaks form\/speed 3.5<b>, watching cream carefully through hole in mixing bowl lid to avoid over-whipping. Spread cream over trifle and decorate with remaining berries and almonds. Cover with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator to chill (minimum of 30 minutes or overnight). Serve chilled."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Jelly","content":["270 g water","5 tsp gelatine powder","450 g red wine","270 g apple juice","120 g caster sugar"]},{"title":"Sponge","content":["butter, for greasing","220 g raw sugar","6 eggs, room temperature","2 tsp natural vanilla extract","½ tsp bicarbonate of soda","1 ½ tsp cream of tartar","130 g gluten free cornflour"]},{"title":"Custard","content":["100 g raw sugar","40 g gluten free cornflour","3 eggs","800 g full cream milk","1 tsp natural vanilla extract"]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["150 g blackberry jam","50 g flaked almonds, toasted","400 g fresh mixed berries","500 g pouring (whipping) cream"]}],"id":"r118212","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-L8hpaffMJVc\/XZWfqoJGlFI\/AAAAAAAAfIQ\/Fk8i2L7vajEIr1N-BVi-1YMi1XjPWHEzgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_zipq9ztdAoBbphjO.png","title":"Berry and red wine trifle","publishedAt":"2016-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"8.6 g","fat":"24.8 g","uom":"pe